@* 
PSEUDOCODE / PLAN (detailed):
1. Create a reusable Blazor component that encapsulates the datasource radio buttons UI.
2. Expose a bindable parameter `Selected` (string) so parent can do two-way binding: `bind-Selected`.
3. Provide an `EventCallback<string> SelectedChanged` (automatically used for bind-Selected) and an optional `EventCallback<string> OnChanged` for additional handling.
4. Keep an internal `_checked` string that is initialized from `Selected` in `OnParametersSet`.
5. Render two `SfRadioButton` controls:
   - Each has `Label`, `Name="options"`, `Value` ("Database" and "AVAPlace").
   - Bind the radio buttons' checked state to `_checked` using `@bind-Checked`.
   - Listen to `@onchange` and forward the new value to `SelectedChanged` and `OnChanged`.
6. Provide a public parameter `LabelText` to allow changing the label text (default "Zdroj dat:").
7. Provide optional `CssClass` parameter to allow styling/overrides.
8. Include local styles for layout similar to original.
9. Keep implementation minimal and safe for use in the existing Scenarios.razor page.
*@

@using Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components

<div class="datasource-selector @CssClass">
    <span class="e-label">@(LabelText ?? "Zdroj dat:")</span>
    <SfRadioButton Label="Databáze" Name="options" Value="Database" @bind-Checked="_checked" @onchange="OnRadioChanged"></SfRadioButton>
    <SfRadioButton Label="AVA Place" Name="options" Value="AVAPlace" @bind-Checked="_checked" @onchange="OnRadioChanged"></SfRadioButton>
</div>